      <title>Motion for Wizard Group Invis</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&amp;message.id=4846#M4846</link>
      <description>Long ago, wizards were one of the first classes to become what I would call masters of invisibility.&amp;nbsp; We got that fancy improved invis back in Kunark I believe that was the envy of many other classes.&amp;nbsp; We could also invis to undead mobs, something that not every invis class could do.&amp;nbsp; Later on, we were one of the first to get a targetted fixed invis called Phase Walk.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; At this point, our invis line stopped growing.&amp;nbsp; Several expansions later, more and more invis spells and AAs started showing up for everybody but us.&amp;nbsp; Druids, Rangers, Shadowknights, Necros, I think even Clerics all got AA invises of varying types.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I still don't understand why the wizard class got overlooked when Depths of Darkhollow AAs were being doled out.&amp;nbsp; Two more expansions passed and with the introduction of Twisted Root, it almost seems as if the AA team didnt know what to give us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;So I propose that we get an invis AA.&amp;nbsp; It only makes sense for it to be regular invis since we're much more the masters of this kind of invis already.&amp;nbsp; Since we were one of the first to get targetted fixed invis, it should also be a group AA.&amp;nbsp; Three cheers for Shared Phase Walk...who's with me?&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
