    <item>
      <title>TSS and beyond ... A Wizard Spell Resists Thread</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&amp;message.id=4815#M4815</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Is it just me, or has the increase in evocation skill not meeting the resist expectations of the new expansion TSS. I was under the impression with the launch of TSS, deterimental spells would not be completly resisted nearly as much. I am maxed in evoc and specialize evoc at 72, and with the new con system, I am still geting fully resisted far to often even by light blues.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I&amp;nbsp;understand resists are part of&amp;nbsp;keeping wizards from being to overpowered, and I agree they have a place in the game... but when you&amp;nbsp;are maxed in crit aa's, focus effects, bard song then see..&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Wizard_01 does a critical blast (22) ... at level 72 is most concerning to me. The new mana regen and harvest are god sends for wizards, no complaint there. &amp;nbsp;But this resist system needs serious attention.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Take for example our new concussion spell. If you can ever get it casted, it ends up resisting 70% of the time. I don't have my alteration up high enough yet, but come on... Lets give a wizard a bone and make these types of spells chromatic!!!!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;How to fix the wizard class lesson 1...&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1. Give us appropiate upgrades to each spell line each level. Having to wait to 75 for a decent fire dd is insane! With each level every other class becomes incrementally more powerful. Wizards do not due to this one inconsistency.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2. Seeing as wizards are the master of the intelligence classes. Give us the unique ability to determine which spell line will work best on mobs. Make mob resist lines random so when a wizard casts on a mob, you recieve a message "Your spell on Mob_01 was [slightly|somewhat|moderatly|highly] effective"&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;With this one change, wizards would become a wanted class in groups and raids again.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3. Make our concussion spells chromatic, and add more abilities like the epic 1.5 to reduce mob resists in a random spell line less likely to resist for a short period of time. Again making us more valuable in groups/raids. God forbid a wizard can do something to prep a raid mob.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;4. for god sakes give us a little utility back!!! you took away mastery of travel from us!. a simple addition of mgb and 2 types of buffs. maybe a buff to increase spell damage or maybe a slight increase in chance to crit dd or melee would be grand!&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;5. Give us some CHOICES when playing. if anything will make wizards happy again will be choices. I don't want to be overpower, I just want some choice and interaction with groups/raids. A great choice would be stances they are talking about for druids. Give us different stances like [mana conserver + less damage], [mana increase/hate increase&amp;nbsp;+ more damage], [mana increase + less resistant]&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;And for complete fun! fix frenzied destruction to be more inline with abilities of our damage parterns like rogues or ranges. At least once or twice a day give us the ability to go completly insane and crit every spell for a minute.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Thats all I have to say...&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
