      <title>TSS spell projections</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&amp;message.id=4748#M4748</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;Disclaimer -- I am not participating in the beta nor have I&#xD;
spoken with any who are participating. I worked up a quick spreadsheet&#xD;
to "project" what the lvl 75 TSS common nukes will be for wizards.&#xD;
Method: 1) Obtained the big nuke for Fire + Magic for wizards for all&#xD;
expansions in which level increased to 60, 65, and 70.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
These expansions were Luclin, PoP, and OoW.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Note --&#xD;
in some cases spell values have changed and the damage amount&#xD;
represents the highest level of spell (non-ancient) available to a&#xD;
wizard at that level and that era.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; I did not go back&#xD;
to the original levels of the spells.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Some spell values&#xD;
have been "adjusted" since original inception. 2) Calculated the ratio&#xD;
between subsequent levels of spells.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; For example,&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
divide the big fire nuke amount for OoW (70), and divide that by the&#xD;
PoP value. 3) Took the most likely ratio (yes there is a pattern) and&#xD;
applied it to the lvl 70 spell to determine the amount of dmg of the&#xD;
spell that would be available to a lvl 75 wizard. Here are the results:&#xD;
60 Luclin 65 Pop 70 OoW 75 Tss Big Fire 2000 2740 3770 5164.9 Big Magic&#xD;
1796 2350 3233 4429.21 draught fire 622 980 1348 1846.76 draught magic&#xD;
688 980 1348 1846.76 draught ice 793 980 1348 1846.76 Note that the&#xD;
most common ratio between subsequent era spells available is&#xD;
~1.37.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; For example: 2740/2000 = 1.375 3770/2740 =&#xD;
1.37 1348/980 = 1.37 2350/1796= 1.37 There are a few differences but&#xD;
overall it seems the most common spell damage raise for&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
expansions that contain new levels is 37 percent. So applying&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
1.37 to the level 70 spells yields the following "projected" values for&#xD;
the wizard spells available to a level 75 TSS era wizard: 75 Tss&#xD;
BigFire 5164.9 Big Magic 4429.21 draught fire 1846.76 draught magic&#xD;
1846.76 draught ice 1846.76 I might go ahead and do the same&#xD;
"projections" for some of the other spells.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; I am sure&#xD;
there will be similar ratios for rains, lures, lure rains,&#xD;
etc.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; I am unsure whether or not "Ether Flame" falls&#xD;
into a different category than "Big Fire". &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; I suspect&#xD;
there may be some change to the "Big Fire" nuke because it would be odd&#xD;
to go "downward" from a previous expansion. &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; So there might&#xD;
be some change with that "projection".&amp;nbsp; Lets see how "predictable"&#xD;
the new spell designer is .......&lt;span&gt; &amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;I&#xD;
certainly hope the spell designer does not follow the same "formula"&#xD;
based method as previous expansions.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; It is clear that the&#xD;
formul method has not served wizards well in previous expansions.</description>
